t11FabricConfigServerMIB.name: t11FabricConfigServerMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

t11FabricConfigServerMIB.contactinfo: Claudio DeSanti Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA EMail: cds@cisco.com Keith McCloghrie Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Email: kzm@cisco.com
t11FabricConfigServerMIB.description: The MIB module for the management of a Fabric Configuration Server (FCS) in a Fibre Channel (FC) network. An FCS is defined by the FC-GS-5 standard. This MIB provides the capabilities to trigger a discovery of the configuration of one or more Fabrics, to retrieve the results of such a discovery, as well as to control and monitor the operation of an FCS. The discovered configuration contains information about: - Interconnect Elements (IEs), i.e., switches, hubs, bridges, etc., - Ports on IEs, and - Platforms which consist of one or more FC nodes.

T11ListIndex.name: T11ListIndex
T11ListIndex.description: An index which identifies a list of elements. All elements which belong to the same list have the same index value. This syntax is used for objects which identify a list in the INDEX clause of a table of elements of that type of list.

T11ListIndexPointer.name: T11ListIndexPointer
T11ListIndexPointer.description: Objects with this syntax point to a list of elements contained in a table, by holding the same value as the object with syntax T11ListIndex defined in the table's INDEX clause, or, zero to indicate an empty list. The definition of an object with this syntax must identify the table(s) into which it points.

FcIeType.name: FcIeType
FcIeType.description: The type of Interconnect Element (IE): unknown(1) - an unknown IE. other(2) - some other type of IE. switch(3) - the IE is a switch. hub(4) - the IE is a hub. bridge(5) - the IE is a bridge.
FcIeType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, Table 124.

FcPortState.name: FcPortState
FcPortState.description: The state of a port: unknown(1) - unknown state. other(2) - some other state. online(3) - port is in online state. offline(4) - port is in offline state. testing(5) - port is in testing state. fault(6) - port is faulty.
FcPortState.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, table 134.

FcPortTxType.name: FcPortTxType
FcPortTxType.description: The technology of the port transceiver: unknown - unknown (includes the 'null' type) other - some other technology shortwave850nm - Short wave laser - SN (850 nm) longwave1550nm - Long wave laser - LL (1550 nm) longwave1310nm - Long wave laser cost reduced - LC (1310 nm) electrical - Electrical - EL.
FcPortTxType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, table 129.

T11FcsRejectReasonExplanation.name: T11FcsRejectReasonExplanation
T11FcsRejectReasonExplanation.description: The reject reason code explanation: noAdditionalExplanation(1) - no additional explanation. invNameIdForIEOrPort(2) - the format of IE or port name is invalid. ieListNotAvailable(3) - IE list is not available. ieTypeNotAvailable(4) - IE type is not available. domainIdNotAvailable(5) - Domain ID is not available. mgmtIdNotAvailable(6) - mgmt ID is not available. fabNameNotAvailable(7) - fabric name is not available. ielogNameNotAvailable(8) - IE logical name is not available. mgmtAddrListNotAvailable(9) - mgmt address list is not available. ieInfoListNotAvailable(10) - IE info list is not available. portListNotAvailable(11) - port list is not available. portTypeNotAvailable(12) - port type is not available. phyPortNumNotAvailable(13) - physical port number is not available. attPortNameListNotAvailable(14) - attached port name list is not available. portStateNotAvailable(15) - port state is not available. unableToRegIELogName(16) - not able to register IE logical name. platformNameNoExist(17) - platform name does not exist. platformNameAlreadyExists(18) - platform name already exists. platformNodeNameNoExists(19) - platform node name does not exist. platformNodeNameAlreadyExists(20) - platform node name already exists. resourceUnavailable(21) - resource unavailable. noEntriesInLunMap(22) - zero entries in OS LUN Map. invalidDeviceNameLength(23) - invalid OS device name length. multipleAttributes(24) - multiple attributes of same type in platform attribute block. invalidAttribBlockLength(25) - invalid platform attribute block length. attributesMissing(26) - required platform attributes not present.
T11FcsRejectReasonExplanation.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, table 152.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTable.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTable
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTable.description: This table contains control information for discovery of fabric configuration by locally-managed switches.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryEntry.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryEntry
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryEntry.description: Control information for discovery by the switch identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeLow.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeLow
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeLow.description: The discovery by a particular switch operates within all existing Fabrics that have a fabric index within a specific range. This object specifies the minimum Fabric index value within that range. This value just represents the lower end of the range and does not necessarily represent any existing fabric.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeHigh.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeHigh
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeHigh.description: The discovery by a particular switch operates within all existing fabrics that have a fabric index within a specific range. This object specifies the maximum fabric index value within that range. This value just represents the higher end of the range and does not necessarily represent any existing fabric.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryStart.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryStart
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryStart.description: This object provides the capability to trigger the start of a discovery by a Fabric Configuration Server. If this object is set to 'start', then the discovery is started on those fabrics which have their fabric index value in the range specified by t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeLow and t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeHigh. Setting this object to 'start' will be rejected if a discovery is already/still in progress on any fabrics in the specified range. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. The value of this object when read is always 'noOp'.

t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut.name: t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut
t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut.description: The minimum interval of time for which the discovered fabric information is cached by a Fabric Configuration Server.

t11FcsDiscoveryStateTable.name: t11FcsDiscoveryStateTable
t11FcsDiscoveryStateTable.description: This table contains the status of discovery for all fabrics known to locally-managed switches.

t11FcsDiscoveryStateEntry.name: t11FcsDiscoveryStateEntry
t11FcsDiscoveryStateEntry.description: The discovery status for a particular fabric on the switch identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex.

t11FcsFabricIndex.name: t11FcsFabricIndex
t11FcsFabricIndex.description: A unique index value which uniquely identifies a particular fabric. In a fabric conformant to FC-SW-4, multiple Virtual Fabrics can operate within one (or more) physical infrastructures, and this index value is used to uniquely identify a particular (physical or virtual) fabric within a physical infrastructure. In a fabric conformant to versions earlier than FC-SW-4, only a single fabric could operate within a physical infrastructure, and thus, the value of this fabric index was defined to always be 1.

t11FcsDiscoveryStatus.name: t11FcsDiscoveryStatus
t11FcsDiscoveryStatus.description: The status of the discovery for the particular fabric. Initially when the switch comes up, all instances of this object have the value: 'localOnly', and the database contains only local information, i.e., no information discovered via the Fabric Configuration Server protocol specified in FC-GS-5. If t11FcsFabricDiscoveryStart is set to 'start' for a range of fabrics which includes this fabric, then the value of this object transitions to 'inProgress'. When the discovery completes, this object transitions to 'completed', and the data is cached for the minimum interval of time specified by t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut. After this interval has been exceeded, the data may be lost, in which case this object is set to 'localOnly'. If a manager sets this object to 'localOnly', the cached data for the fabric is discarded immediately, and if a discovery was in progress for this fabric, then that discovery is aborted.

t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteTime.name: t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteTime
t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteTime.description: This object contains the value of sysUpTime at which discovery was most recently completed or aborted on this fabric. This object contains the value of zero before the first discovery on this fabric.

t11FcsIeTable.name: t11FcsIeTable
t11FcsIeTable.description: A table of Interconnect Elements. Interconnect Elements (IEs) are switches, hubs, bridges etc. By default, the Fabric Configuration Server will maintain detailed information pertaining only to local resources. As far as remote topology is concerned, only the IE name, type and domain-id information will be maintained. If a discovery cycle is triggered on a set of fabrics, this table along with the Port and Platform tables will be populated with the discovered information. The discovered data will be retained in this table for at least t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut seconds after the completion of its discovery or till the discovered data is invalidated.

t11FcsIeEntry.name: t11FcsIeEntry
t11FcsIeEntry.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.
t11FcsIeEntry.description: Information about an Interconnect Element which was discovered on a fabric (identified by t11FcsFabricIndex), by a switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsIeName.name: t11FcsIeName
t11FcsIeName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.1.
t11FcsIeName.description: The WWN of an Interconnect Element. This object uniquely identifies an Interconnect Element on a fabric. If the IE is a switch, then this object is the Node WWN of the switch.

t11FcsIeType.name: t11FcsIeType
t11FcsIeType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.2
t11FcsIeType.description: The type of this Interconnect Element.

t11FcsIeDomainId.name: t11FcsIeDomainId
t11FcsIeDomainId.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.3.
t11FcsIeDomainId.description: The Domain Id of this Interconnect Element.

t11FcsIeMgmtId.name: t11FcsIeMgmtId
t11FcsIeMgmtId.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.4.
t11FcsIeMgmtId.description: The management identifer of this Interconnect Element. If the Interconnect Element is a switch, this object will be the Domain Controller identifier of the switch. When the value of the identifier is unknown, this object contains the all-zeros value: x'00 00 00'.

t11FcsIeFabricName.name: t11FcsIeFabricName
t11FcsIeFabricName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.5.
t11FcsIeFabricName.description: The fabric name of this Interconnect Element. When the fabric name is unknown, this object contains the all-zeros value: x'00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00'.

t11FcsIeLogicalName.name: t11FcsIeLogicalName
t11FcsIeLogicalName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.6.
t11FcsIeLogicalName.description: The logical name of this Interconnect Element. When the logical name is unknown, this object contains the zero-length string.

t11FcsIeMgmtAddrListIndex.name: t11FcsIeMgmtAddrListIndex
t11FcsIeMgmtAddrListIndex.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.7.
t11FcsIeMgmtAddrListIndex.description: The management address list for this Interconnect Element. This object points to an entry in the t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable.

t11FcsIeInfoList.name: t11FcsIeInfoList
t11FcsIeInfoList.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.8
t11FcsIeInfoList.description: The information list for this Interconnect Element. This object contains the following substrings in order: vendor name, model name/number and release code/level, followed by zero or more substrings of vendor-specific information. Each substring is terminated with a byte containing a null value (x'00').

t11FcsIePortListIndex.name: t11FcsIePortListIndex
t11FcsIePortListIndex.description: The port list for this Interconnect Element. This object points to an entry in the t11FcsPortListTable.

t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable
t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable.description: This table contains the set of management address lists which are currently referenced by any instance of the t11FcsIeMgmtAddrListIndex or t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex objects.

t11FcsMgmtAddrListEntry.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrListEntry
t11FcsMgmtAddrListEntry.description: Information about one management address in a management address list, which is known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsMgmtAddrListIndex.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrListIndex
t11FcsMgmtAddrListIndex.description: The index value of the management address list.

t11FcsMgmtAddrIndex.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrIndex
t11FcsMgmtAddrIndex.description: An integer value to distinguish different management addresses in the same list.

t11FcsMgmtAddr.name: t11FcsMgmtAddr
t11FcsMgmtAddr.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.2.7
t11FcsMgmtAddr.description: The management address of this entry. The format of this object may be based on the format of the Uniform Resource Locator (URL). For example, for SNMP, see RFC 4088.

t11FcsPortListTable.name: t11FcsPortListTable
t11FcsPortListTable.description: This table contains all the lists of ports that are associated with Interconnect Elements contained in t11FcsIeTable.

t11FcsPortListEntry.name: t11FcsPortListEntry
t11FcsPortListEntry.description: An entry which identifies that the port which has the port name, t11FcsPortName, is in a particular list of ports, which is known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsPortListIndex.name: t11FcsPortListIndex
t11FcsPortListIndex.description: The index value of the port list.

t11FcsPortTable.name: t11FcsPortTable
t11FcsPortTable.description: This table contains information the ports which are grouped into lists by the t11FcsPortListTable.

t11FcsPortEntry.name: t11FcsPortEntry
t11FcsPortEntry.description: Information about a particular port, which is connected to a fabric (identified by t11FcsFabricIndex) and known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsPortName.name: t11FcsPortName
t11FcsPortName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.1.
t11FcsPortName.description: The WWN of the port for whcih this entry contains information.

t11FcsPortType.name: t11FcsPortType
t11FcsPortType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.2.
t11FcsPortType.description: The Port Type of this port.

t11FcsPortTXType.name: t11FcsPortTXType
t11FcsPortTXType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.3.
t11FcsPortTXType.description: The TX type of this port.

t11FcsPortModuleType.name: t11FcsPortModuleType
t11FcsPortModuleType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.4.
t11FcsPortModuleType.description: The port module type of this port.

t11FcsPortPhyPortNum.name: t11FcsPortPhyPortNum
t11FcsPortPhyPortNum.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.5.
t11FcsPortPhyPortNum.description: The physical number for this port.

t11FcsPortAttachPortNameIndex.name: t11FcsPortAttachPortNameIndex
t11FcsPortAttachPortNameIndex.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.6.
t11FcsPortAttachPortNameIndex.description: The attached port name list for this port. This object points to an entry in the t11FcsAttachPortNameListTable.

t11FcsPortState.name: t11FcsPortState
t11FcsPortState.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.7.

t11FcsPortSpeedCapab.name: t11FcsPortSpeedCapab
t11FcsPortSpeedCapab.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.8.
t11FcsPortSpeedCapab.description: The port speed capabilities of this port. The two octets of the value are formatted as described in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsPortOperSpeed.name: t11FcsPortOperSpeed
t11FcsPortOperSpeed.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.9.
t11FcsPortOperSpeed.description: The operating speed of this port. The two octets of the value are formatted as described in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsPortZoningEnfStatus.name: t11FcsPortZoningEnfStatus
t11FcsPortZoningEnfStatus.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.10.
t11FcsPortZoningEnfStatus.description: The zoning enforcement status of this port.. The twelve octets of the value are formatted as described in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsAttachPortNameListTable.name: t11FcsAttachPortNameListTable
t11FcsAttachPortNameListTable.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.6
t11FcsAttachPortNameListTable.description: This table contains all the lists of attach port names.

t11FcsAttachPortNameListEntry.name: t11FcsAttachPortNameListEntry
t11FcsAttachPortNameListEntry.description: Information about teh name of a particular attached port, which is known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsAttachPortNameListIndex.name: t11FcsAttachPortNameListIndex
t11FcsAttachPortNameListIndex.description: The index value of the attach port name list.

t11FcsAttachPortName.name: t11FcsAttachPortName
t11FcsAttachPortName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.3.6
t11FcsAttachPortName.description: The attached port name. Zero or more of these names may be associated with a port object. The first 8 bytes of this object contain the WWN of the port followed by 2 reserved bytes. Following this is one byte of Port flags and one byte of Port type, as described in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsPlatformTable.name: t11FcsPlatformTable
t11FcsPlatformTable.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4
t11FcsPlatformTable.description: This table contains information on platforms. By default, this table only contains information about a locally-managed switch. If a discovery is triggered, this table will also contain the information gathered by the discovery process. The discovered information is retained in this table for at least t11FcsFabricDiscoveryTimeOut seconds after the completion of its discovery or until the discovered cache is invalidated.

t11FcsPlatformEntry.name: t11FcsPlatformEntry
t11FcsPlatformEntry.description: Information about a particular platform, which is known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex). A platform can contain multiple nodes. Information on nodes is contained in the t11FcsNodeNameListTable. The t11FcsPlatformNodeNameListIndex object in this table points to the list of nodes contained in this platform. Similarly, the t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex object in this table points to the list of management addresses associated with this platform.

t11FcsPlatformIndex.name: t11FcsPlatformIndex
t11FcsPlatformIndex.description: An integer value to distinguish one platform from other platforms in the same fabric.

t11FcsPlatformName.name: t11FcsPlatformName
t11FcsPlatformName.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.2
t11FcsPlatformName.description: The name of this platform. The last byte of the value indicates the format of the name, as specified in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsPlatformType.name: t11FcsPlatformType
t11FcsPlatformType.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.3
t11FcsPlatformType.description: The type(s) of this platform, encoded in four bytes as specified in FC-GS-5.

t11FcsPlatformNodeNameListIndex.name: t11FcsPlatformNodeNameListIndex
t11FcsPlatformNodeNameListIndex.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.6
t11FcsPlatformNodeNameListIndex.description: The list of nodes for this platform. This object points to an entry in the t11FcsNodeNameListTable.

t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex.name: t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex
t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.7
t11FcsPlatformMgmtAddrListIndex.description: The list of management addresses for this platform. This object points to an entry in the t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable.

t11FcsPlatformVendorId.name: t11FcsPlatformVendorId
t11FcsPlatformVendorId.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformVendorId.description: The identifier of the vendor of this platform.

t11FcsPlatformProductId.name: t11FcsPlatformProductId
t11FcsPlatformProductId.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformProductId.description: The vendor's product and/or model identifier for this platform.

t11FcsPlatformProductRevLevel.name: t11FcsPlatformProductRevLevel
t11FcsPlatformProductRevLevel.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformProductRevLevel.description: The product revision level for this platform.

t11FcsPlatformDescription.name: t11FcsPlatformDescription
t11FcsPlatformDescription.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.10
t11FcsPlatformDescription.description: The description of this platform. This value should include the full name and version identification of the platform's hardware type and software operating system.

t11FcsPlatformLabel.name: t11FcsPlatformLabel
t11FcsPlatformLabel.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.11
t11FcsPlatformLabel.description: An administratively assigned symbolic name for the platform.

t11FcsPlatformLocation.name: t11FcsPlatformLocation
t11FcsPlatformLocation.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.12
t11FcsPlatformLocation.description: The physical location of the platform (e.g., 'telephone closet, 3rd floor').

t11FcsPlatformSystemID.name: t11FcsPlatformSystemID
t11FcsPlatformSystemID.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformSystemID.description: An identifier for a hosting system that this platform is associated with. This identifier is used to associate platforms of logical types (e.g., logical partitions) with a physical system.

t11FcsPlatformSysMgmtAddr.name: t11FcsPlatformSysMgmtAddr
t11FcsPlatformSysMgmtAddr.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformSysMgmtAddr.description: A list of management addresses for the platform.

t11FcsPlatformClusterId.name: t11FcsPlatformClusterId
t11FcsPlatformClusterId.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformClusterId.description: An identifier for a cluster that this platform is associated with, where a cluster is a set of independent platforms that are managed together to provide increased performance capabilities, failover, etc.

t11FcsPlatformClusterMgmtAddr.name: t11FcsPlatformClusterMgmtAddr
t11FcsPlatformClusterMgmtAddr.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformClusterMgmtAddr.description: A list of management addresses for the cluster identified in the corresponding instance of t11FcsPlatformClusterId.

t11FcsPlatformFC4Types.name: t11FcsPlatformFC4Types
t11FcsPlatformFC4Types.reference: ANSI NCITS xxx-200x, Fibre Channel - Generic Services 5, FC-GS-5 T11/Project 1677-D/Rev 8, section 6.2.3.4.5
t11FcsPlatformFC4Types.description: The FC-4 types supported by this platform, formatted as a bit mask as specified in FC-GS-5. If this object contains the zero-length string, the types are unknown.

t11FcsNodeNameListTable.name: t11FcsNodeNameListTable
t11FcsNodeNameListTable.description: This table contains all the lists of nodes.

t11FcsNodeNameListEntry.name: t11FcsNodeNameListEntry
t11FcsNodeNameListEntry.description: Information about a node, which is known to a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsNodeNameListIndex.name: t11FcsNodeNameListIndex
t11FcsNodeNameListIndex.description: The index value of the node name list.

t11FcsStatsTable.name: t11FcsStatsTable
t11FcsStatsTable.description: This table contains all the statistics related to the Fabric Configuration Server.

t11FcsStatsEntry.name: t11FcsStatsEntry
t11FcsStatsEntry.description: A set of statistics for a particular fabric (identified by t11FcsFabricIndex) on a locally-managed switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsRxGetReqs.name: t11FcsRxGetReqs
t11FcsRxGetReqs.description: The number of Get Requests received by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsTxGetReqs.name: t11FcsTxGetReqs
t11FcsTxGetReqs.description: The number of Get Requests sent by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric to other servers in the fabric.

t11FcsRxRegReqs.name: t11FcsRxRegReqs
t11FcsRxRegReqs.description: The number of Registration Requests received by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsTxRegReqs.name: t11FcsTxRegReqs
t11FcsTxRegReqs.description: The number of Registration Requests sent by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsRxDeregReqs.name: t11FcsRxDeregReqs
t11FcsRxDeregReqs.description: The number of Deregistration Requests received by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsTxDeregReqs.name: t11FcsTxDeregReqs
t11FcsTxDeregReqs.description: The number of Deregistration Requests sent by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsTxRscns.name: t11FcsTxRscns
t11FcsTxRscns.description: The number of Registered State Change Notifications (RSCNs) sent by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsRxRscns.name: t11FcsRxRscns
t11FcsRxRscns.description: The number of Registered State Change Notifications (RSCNs) received by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsRejects.name: t11FcsRejects
t11FcsRejects.description: The total number of requests rejected by the Fabric Configuration Server on this fabric.

t11FcsNotifyControlTable.name: t11FcsNotifyControlTable
t11FcsNotifyControlTable.description: A table of control information for notifications generated due to Fabric Configuration Server events.

t11FcsNotifyControlEntry.name: t11FcsNotifyControlEntry
t11FcsNotifyControlEntry.description: Each entry contains notification control information for a Fabric Configuration Server on a particular fabric (identified by t11FcsFabricIndex) on a particular switch (identified by fcmInstanceIndex and fcmSwitchIndex).

t11FcsReqRejectNotifyEnable.name: t11FcsReqRejectNotifyEnable
t11FcsReqRejectNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if the Fabric Configuration Server should generate 't11FcsReqectRejNotify' notifications. If the value of this object is 'true', then the notification is issued. If the value of this object is 'false', then the notification is not issued.

t11FcsDiscoveryCompNotifyEnable.name: t11FcsDiscoveryCompNotifyEnable
t11FcsDiscoveryCompNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if the Fabric Configuration Server should generate 't11FcsDiscoveryCompleteNotify' notifications. If the value of this object is 'true', then the notification is issued. If the value of this object is 'false', then the notification is not issued.

t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotifyEnable.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotifyEnable
t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if the Fabric Configuration Server should generate 't11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotify' notifications. If the value of this object is 'true', then the notification is issued. If the value of this object is 'false', then the notification is not issued.

t11FcsRejectCtCommandString.name: t11FcsRejectCtCommandString
t11FcsRejectCtCommandString.description: The binary content of the Fabric Configuration Server request, formatted as an octet string (in network byte order) containing the CT_IU, as described in Table 2 of FC-GS-5 (including the preamble), which was most recently rejected by the Fabric Configuration Server for this fabric. This object contains the zero-length string if and when the CT-IU's content is unavailable. When the length of this object is 255 octets, it contains the first 255 octets of the CT-IU (in network-byte order).

t11FcsRejectRequestSource.name: t11FcsRejectRequestSource
t11FcsRejectRequestSource.description: The WWN which was the source of the CT_IU contained in the corresponding instance of t11FcsRejectCtCommandString.

t11FcsRejectReasonCode.name: t11FcsRejectReasonCode
t11FcsRejectReasonCode.description: This object contains the reason code corresponding to the latest Fabric Configuration Server request rejected by the local system.

t11FcsRejectReasonCodeExp.name: t11FcsRejectReasonCodeExp
t11FcsRejectReasonCodeExp.description: When the corresponding instance of t11FcsRejectReasonCode has the value: 'unable to perform command request', this object contains the corresponding reason code explanation.

t11FcsReqRejectNotify.name: t11FcsReqRejectNotify
t11FcsReqRejectNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever the Fabric Configuration Server on a switch (indicated by the value of t11FamLocalSwitchWwn) rejects a Fabric Configuration Server request. The Fabric Configuration Server should update the t11FcsRejReasonCode and t11FcsRejReasonCodeExplanation objects with the corresponding reason code and reason code explanation before sending the notification.

t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteNotify.name: t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteNotify
t11FcsDiscoveryCompleteNotify.description: This notification is generated by the Fabric Configuration Server on the completion of the discovery of fabrics in the range which has t11FcsFabricDiscoveryRangeLow at its low end.

t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotify.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotify
t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeNotify.description: This notification is generated by the Fabric Configuration Server whenever the management address of an IE changes, i.e., whenever an entry in the t11FcsMgmtAddrListTable changes.

t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeFabricIndex.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeFabricIndex
t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeFabricIndex.description: The index value which identifies the fabric on which a management address change has been detected.

t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeIeName.name: t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeIeName
t11FcsMgmtAddrChangeIeName.description: The IE for which a management address change has been detected.

t11FcsMIBCompliance.name: t11FcsMIBCompliance
t11FcsMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Fabric Configuration Server.

t11FcsDiscoveryControlGroup.name: t11FcsDiscoveryControlGroup
t11FcsDiscoveryControlGroup.description: A collection of objects for requesting a Fabric Configuration Server to discover the configuration of one or more fabrics.

t11FcsDiscoveryStatusGroup.name: t11FcsDiscoveryStatusGroup
t11FcsDiscoveryStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects with which to monitor the status of discovery (of fabric configurations) by Fabric Configuration Servers.

t11FcsDiscoveredConfigGroup.name: t11FcsDiscoveredConfigGroup
t11FcsDiscoveredConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to contain the fabric configuration information discovered by Fabric Configuration Servers.

t11FcsStatisticsGroup.name: t11FcsStatisticsGroup
t11FcsStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects for Fabric Configuration Server statistics information.

t11FcsNotificationInfoGroup.name: t11FcsNotificationInfoGroup
t11FcsNotificationInfoGroup.description: A collection of notification control and notification information objects for monitoring Fabric Configuration Server request rejection and discovery of remote toplogy information.

t11FcsNotificationGroup.name: t11FcsNotificationGroup
t11FcsNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications for monitoring Fabric Configuration Servers.
